#: ../../configuration_server/antivirus_configuration.rst:96
msgid "ClamAV runs in one of three modes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../configuration_server/antivirus_configuration.rst:98
msgid ""
"Daemon (Socket): ClamAV is running on the same server as ownCloud. The "
"ClamAV daemon, ``clamd``, runs in the background. When there is no "
"activity ``clamd`` places a minimal load on your system. If your users "
"upload large volumes of files you will see high CPU usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../configuration_server/antivirus_configuration.rst:103
msgid ""
"Daemon: ClamAV is running on a different server. This is a good option "
"for ownCloud servers with high volumes of file uploads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../configuration_server/antivirus_configuration.rst:106
msgid ""
"Executable: ClamAV is running on the same server as ownCloud, and the "
"``clamscan`` command is started and then stopped with each file upload. "
"``clamscan`` is slow and not always reliable for on-demand usage; it is "
"better to use one of the daemon modes."
msgstr ""

